<section id="data-governance" class="data-governance">
    <h2>Data Governance</h2>
    <p>Data Governance is the exercise of authority and control (planning, monitoring, and enforcement) over the management of data assets. It ensures that data delivers value and supports the organization’s goals.</p>
    <p><strong>Why is Data Governance Critical?</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Increased volume of data from various sources</li>
        <li>Improved decision-making through reliable information</li>
        <li>Ensures compliance with regulatory standards</li>
        <li>Provides competitive advantage through better use of data</li>
        <li>Addresses risks and ensures data security</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Benefits of Data Governance:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Reduces compliance risks</li>
        <li>Improves data quality and accessibility</li>
        <li>Enhances agility and ability to respond to change</li>
    </ul>
